["Erhard \"Sepp\" Wunderlich (December 14, 1956 \u2013 October 4, 2012) was a German handball player.[1]","Wunderlich was born in Augsburg.  As a member of the West German handball team, he won the 1978 World Men's Handball Championship and the silver medal at the 1984 Summer Olympics. At the latter tournament he played all six matches and scored 22 goals.","He played club handball for the VfL Gummersbach from 1976 to 1983 when he left to join FC Barcelona. He later returned to Germany to play for the TSV Milbertshofen. During his club career he won four European Cups and two German Championships. In 1999 he was voted German Handballer of the Century.[2]","He died, aged 55, in Cologne of skin cancer.[2] He was buried in his home town Augsburg, as was his last wish, on 10 October 2012.[3]","This article about a handball Olympic medalist for Germany is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it."]